<!--
    With the structuire of the routes above we can have SEO friendly urls like the ones below:
        - /accommodation/Banff
        - /destinations/Canada
        - /destinations/Canada/Alberta
        - /destinations/Canada/Alberta/Banff
        - /destinations/Alberta
        - /destinations/Alberta/Banff
        - /destinations/Banff
    The redirect to the '/accomodations'' route will always use the last non-null token in the route as the 'location' filter.

    Ideally, external links should be culture agnostic (no culture in the url) but this redirect will still work if it is included.
        - /en/accommodation/Banff
        - /en/destinations/Canada
        - /en/destinations/Canada/Alberta
        - /en/destinations/Canada/Alberta/Banff
-->
